               <p>It appear'd by the Evidence, that the Prisoner went to drink at the Prosecutor's House, and pretending to have Occasion to go into the Prosecutor's Yard, took the Sauce-pan, and having ty'd it with his Garter round his Waste, under his Coat, was going off with it, but was discover'd by the Handle hanging out.</p>
               <p>The Fact being plain against the Prisoner, he was found <rs id="t17310908-68-verdict330" type="verdictDescription">
